{
  "stem": "19550.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 202.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she was an extraordinarily beautiful and sensitive [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] girl.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we all poured our whole existence into her.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We all saw in her the incarnation of the best that we had.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And all our hopes and, and aspirations were concentrated and distilled in her.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] perhaps unconsciously, hoped that whatever fate befell us, she we will see a better day.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She will live in a more human world, in a more humane world.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] That she was lost is somehow the greatest loss to us because she was the quintessential [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] impersonation and, and, and incarnation of all that we were and all that we wanted to be and all that we hope to be and all that we hoped for for the Jews, for humanity, and for the world.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It's extremely difficult for us to this day [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to, in the first place, see her as-- right now, she would be a woman in her late 50s or something like that, or 60s.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We, of course, always see her as, as we saw her then, and we can't make our peace with her not being.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] Perhaps it's the same with other families, too.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] To us, she was all.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And in a very real sense, she really still is.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We don't exist without her, because she exists and will for us always [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in a very real way, the same as my mother.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, obviously, everybody was-- just the town was in an uproar.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People were wrought up, completely bewildered, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] really without council.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
